result.execSummary:
The defendant Phillip R Kuehn was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Battery [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse, Repeater], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Phillip D. Kuehn in court with attorney Jessica L Schuster.  Ralph Malcom Uttke appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called @ 4:06 p.m. Agreement stated - Def will plead to ct 1, ct 2 dismiss and read in, withheld sentence, 1 yr probation, counseling, court costs. State has complied with VWNR. State advises that Def's middle initial is R. Def verifies. Court directs COC to correct record to Phillip R. Kuehn. Atty Schuster and Def agree with stated agreement. Plea quest reviewed. Plea to ct 1 - no contest. Ct 2 dismissed and read in on motion of State. Constitutional rights, elements, possible penalties reviewed. Atty Schuster satisfied. Court finds Def understands and plea freely & voluntarily made. Factual basis. Court accepts plea and finds guilty of ct 1. Sentencing remarks by Counsel. Nothing by Defendant. Remarks by the Court, will follow agreement. Withheld sentence, 1 yr probation, counseling as recommended, court costs, DNA sample and surcharge, 1 day credit if revoked.   If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered, without further order of the court, against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt. Postconviction rights. Def to report to probation first thing tomorrow morning.

Defendant Phillip D. Kuehn not in court.  Ralph Malcom Uttke appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court calls  @ 3:05 pm.  State moves to lift the no contact provision with T.K.  Court will approve request & will delete no contact provision with T.K. be lifted.
